ActParliamentary Employment and Staff Relations Act
SubjectOrder Designating the Leader of the Government in the House of Commons as the Minister for the Purposes of the Parliamentary Employment and Staff Relations Act
PrecisOrder (1) repealing Order in Council P.C. 2025-88 of February 12, 2025; and (2) designating the Leader of the Government in the House of Commons, a member of the King’s Privy Council for Canada, for the purposes of the PARLIAMENTARY EMPLOYMENT AND STAFF RELATIONS ACT.
